<dc:date>2008-09-27T21:39:09+00:00</dc:date>
<dc:subject>journal</dc:subject>
</item>

<item rdf:about="http://use.perl.org/~brian_d_foy/journal/37512?from=rss">
<title>cpan script now in github, with new features</title>
<link>http://use.perl.org/~brian_d_foy/journal/37512?from=rss</link>
<description>&lt;p&gt;I've move my &lt;code&gt;cpan&lt;/code&gt; script into &lt;a href="http://github.com/briandfoy/cpan-script/tree/master"&gt;its own github repository&lt;/a&gt; since I got a burst of feature requests. I also change it to use the &lt;code&gt;App::*&lt;/code&gt; structure.&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p&gt;There are some new switches:&lt;/p&gt;&lt;ul&gt;&lt;li&gt;-j filename  --&amp;gt; load an alternate CPAN configuration&lt;/li&gt;&lt;li&gt;-J --&amp;gt; dump the current CPAN configuration, including anything changed during the run&lt;/li&gt;&lt;li&gt;-l --&amp;gt; list all of the installed modules&lt;/li&gt;&lt;li&gt;-g --&amp;gt; download the module tarball, but then stop&lt;/li&gt;&lt;/ul&gt;&lt;p&gt;It's going to stay in the repo for a bit while I fix up a few things, but you can play with the sources if you like&lt;nobr&gt; &lt;wbr&gt;&lt;/nobr&gt;:)&lt;/p&gt;</description>
<dc:creator>brian_d_foy</dc:creator>
<dc:date>2008-09-22T20:44:13+00:00</dc:date>
<dc:subject>journal</dc:subject>
</item>

